<Author>Helking
<Content>Modern, Clean and Central A group of 8 of us stayed in 4 rooms at the Splendid. The rooms we had were all quiet despite a couple of them facing the front of the hotel. Our room was facing a central light well and was exceptionally quiet. All of the rooms we had ranged from reasonably sized to quite large and all were very modern and clean. The bathrooms are lovely all marble and a good size with an excellent range of toiletries and amenities for a hotel of this rating. We didn't have breakfast in the hotel as there are plenty of more reasonably priced options within walking distance including a very nice cafe across the road. The hotel is in an excellent location literally a few minutes walk from Univerity Square, where there is a metro stop. Placa de la catalunya, La Rambla, Passieg De Gracia and much more are all within easy walking distance, even Port Vell and Barceloneta can be easily reached on foot for those who like to walk a little. The only thing that I felt the hotel lacked was a lounge area although this was not a major problem it would have been nice to have somewhere we could all sit and wait to meet up. The staff were all very friendly and helpful and I would definitely recommend this hotel as it is an excellent option for the price. A couple of tips, book directly with the hotel online to get the best price. The Aerobus from the airport stops at University Sqaure a few minutes walk and is very reasonable. 
