<Content>Very pleasant stay at the Splendid We stayed at the Splendid for 1 night prior to a cruise. The Hotel had been booked for us by our Cruise Agent and having read some mixed reviews on Trip Advisor we went with a very open mind.The Apsis Splendid is in no way a luxury hotel but perfectly adequate for a short stay in Barcelona. Our room was small but well appointed and on the back of the hotel with a view onto a central shaft but the bonus was the room was very quiet. The bathroom was very nice and spacious fully tiled with marble effect tiles. The shower was over the bath and there was a good range of complimentary toiletries. Everywhere was spotlessly clean.The breakfast was a simple buffet with breads, cereals some fruits and hot dishes. Since it was included in the price we had no complaints.The only problem with this hotel is that whilst it is not too far from Catalunya Square it is all too easy to get lost on the way making it quite a long walk!A warning to everyone going to Barcelona - there was a gent in the reception at the hotel calling the police to report his wallett had been stolen - having been there before and having heard numerous stories of such events we were extra cautious. Barcelona must be the pick-pocket capital of the world. My advice is if anyone stops you to speak keep walking - not very nice I know but it seems the best approach. 
