<Content>Splendid? Yes! I have stayed at the Hotel Apsis Splendid twice, most recently in December 2004. I highly recommend the Splendid. This is a clean, modern hotel in a great location. Our room was spotless, comfortable and quiet. Placa Catalunya and La Rambla are a short walk from the hotel. The Metro station is right around the corner.Do check their website for rates and deals: hotel-splendidIn December, we paid only 70 Euros per night for a double room. I booked the breakfast online and saved fifty percent鈥攐nly six Euros per person. The breakfast is very good with a wide variety of choices. The staff is friendly and helpful.The area is very safe but I will make one tiny suggestion: Late at night, do not go wandering in El Raval unless you know where you are going. The hotel faces Placa Goya and late at night, across the Placa, you will find some interesting characters. Stick to the main streets.Here is a great website for taking a virtual walk through the neighborhood: Pages Jaunes: Photos de Villes.photos.pagesjaunes.frSelect Barcelona and enter the address of the hotel (Muntaner 2). From there you can navigate the immediate neighborhood and all of Barcelona (or Paris, or Madrid or many other cities.) Or, enter just the street name and cruise straight down the street! 
